  "text": "We compare the proposed COSiNeMax method (Algorithm 1) with three baselines. (1) Random. Uniformly at random selection of k seed nodes. (2) Degree. The top-k nodes with the highest out-degrees. (3) Individual InfMax. In this baseline approach, we follow the voter model over signed networks [CITATION_1] , however we consider each target set separately. That is, we first compute the topk/2 seed nodes so to maximize the spread of the idea O 1 in the target partition V 1 . Next, we find another top-k/2 seed nodes that maximize the spread of the idea O 2 within the target set V 2 . Therefore, by comparing with the Individual Influence Maximization approach as described above, we demonstrate the improvements due to our algorithm COSiNeMax, which returns the top-k optimal seed nodes considering the spread of two contrasting ideas O 1 and O 2 simultaneously.",
